  "text": "In contrast, significant mtDNA depletion, mitochondrial ultrastructural damage, and increased LV mass were found in TMPK TGs treated with AZT. Cardiac overexpression of TMPK, the rate-limiting enzyme in the pathway converting AZT to AZTTP, may have resulted in increased AZTTP levels, which can directly inhibit pol g. [CITATION_1] However, these experiments offer no direct evidence (ie measurement of dTTP pools) to support this conclusion.",
